Zak moved slowly down the street, looking in all directions at the ruins and destruction. The Terran Embassy was just down the street from his position. His squad had fanned out amongst the ruins, and were covering the area. The occasional brief burst of suppressed fire whispered through the ruins, and Zak nodded with pride.<br>
The Terran Embassy was one of the few mostly untouched buildings in the ruins of the city, and for a moment Zak wondered why. Then he saw movement in the shadows, and drew his blades.<br>
What stepped out was a figure from the past, tall and powerful. Zak dropped his weapons as he collapsed to his knees, clutching at his head. The madness had arisen again, and he felt as though a hand had reached into his head, crushing his mind in a grasp of steel.<br>
'So, mighty warrior. You have returned to us' spoke the figure, the voice of death. 'I often thought that you might have died honourably on the field of battle. But when my scouts reported a man with whirling blades of power and speed, I knew that you were on this ball of dust.'<br>
'D'Archon...' Zak murmured as he rose from the ground. 'What you did to me cannot go unpunished. I have grown stronger, much stronger. If you fight me now, this will not be as our old days. I will crush you.' The utter conviction with which he spoke stopped D'Archon's advance for a moment, but the black being simply laughed and strode forwards again.<br>
Zak threw up his hand, and D'Archon was flung backwards into the wall of the embassy by a burst of sheer power. Zak calmly stooped to retrieve his weapons, and D'Archon drew his greatsword of purest shadow. With a psychic roar that resounded down the street, loud enough to shake the entire ship and cause Zorbus to collapse in seizures, the two warriors charged, blades flickering, each probing weaknesses in the other's defence. <p>'It's better to light a candle than curse the darkness, and better than both to remain unseen.'- NeoAngel. .................

