His twinned blades once more crackled with energy. His torn jacket revealed a metallic implant in his spine as he spun around, a syringe embedded under his skin. As his blades crossed in the air, it hissed and injected a fluid of his own devising into his spinal cord. As his eyes began to glow with a harsh red light, his muscles bulged as the physical enhancer took affect. He grew to match D'Archons height and bulk, and his motions became more fluid.<br>
'The neural interface enhancer! They destroyed the test samples!' D'Archon gasped through his mask. 'How did you procure one?'<br>
'That's an easy one. I was one of the test samples. They removed my long-term memory, and put me in the fighting pits. But I survived. All my memory is encrypted in the hilts of these blades!' Zak cried as his swords pierced D'Archon's body, one through his throat, one effortlessly batting aside his great sword and plunging into his left eye. Zak released the hilts and collapsed to the ground, his body returning to normal as he began to spasm and blood trickled out of his nose and mouth. <p>'It's better to light a candle than curse the darkness, and better than both to remain unseen.'- NeoAngel. .................

